INSERT INTO `quiz_question` VALUES (101,'<p>A&nbsp;<strong>differential reinforcement</strong>&nbsp;procedure where the inter-trial interval has increased such that the rate of behavior has <strong><u>decreased</u></strong> is referred to as...?</p>','2018-05-30 03:03:57','<p><strong>Differential Reinforcement of OTHER behavior (DRO)</strong>&nbsp;is the provision of reinforcement contingent upon any / all behaviors&nbsp;<u>excluding</u>&nbsp;a specific behavior. For example, you might provide a reinforcer every 5 minutes as long as a client has not engaged in aggressive behavior (hitting, kicking, slapping).</p>

<p>DROs may inadvertently reinforce undesired behaviors.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Differential Reinforcement of ALTERNATIVE&nbsp;</strong>behavior (<strong>DRA</strong>) is the provision of reinforcement contingent upon a specific behavior occurring. Typically, but not always, this is the same functional reinforcer as a behavior that might be simultaneously targeted for reduction.</p>

<p><em>Here&#39;s a link to an excellent video featuring <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PQE1RyFziv4&amp;t=1s">Dr. Timothy Vollmer discussing differential reinforcement of alternative behavior</a>, a research focus of his at his lab at the University of Florida.</em></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Differential Reinforcement of HIGHER or LOWER rates of behavior</strong>&nbsp;(<strong>DRH&nbsp;/ DRL</strong>) are both procedures that depend on the inter-trial interval of behavior, which might be a little confusing just looking at the name alone (i.e., the whole&nbsp;<em>rate</em>&nbsp;part). Yes, you are trying to reduce the rate of behavior, however responses are only reinforced if a specific latency has occurred since the last response. Therefore, you&#39;re really just trying to increase / decrease the inter-trial interval (&quot;gap&quot;) between responses, which will, as a product, increase or decrease the rate, of course.&nbsp;</p>',5,1,26,7);
INSERT INTO `quiz_question` VALUES (102,'<p>A&nbsp;<strong>differential reinforcement</strong>&nbsp;procedure where the inter-trial interval has increased such that the rate of behavior has <strong><u>increased</u></strong> is referred to as...?</p>','2018-05-30 03:07:21','<p><strong>Differential Reinforcement of OTHER behavior (DRO)</strong>&nbsp;is the provision of reinforcement contingent upon any / all behaviors&nbsp;<u>excluding</u>&nbsp;a specific behavior. For example, you might provide a reinforcer every 5 minutes as long as a client has not engaged in aggressive behavior (hitting, kicking, slapping).</p>

