<p>There are many types of <strong>preference assssments</strong> - here are the different types:</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>Trial Based Preference Assessments</h2>

<p>Sometimes, behavior analysts will conduct formal preference assessments using the discrete-trial methodology: presenting a formal antecedent, expecting a response - in this case, a selection, and consequating that response with access to the selected stimulus. What follows are preference assessments in the &quot;trial-based&quot; format:</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h3><strong>Multiple Stimulus <u>WITH</u>&nbsp;Replacement</strong></h3>

