<p>Timothy places the picture of his favorite toy truck in Bobby&#39;s hands, and Bobby gives him the toy truck.</p>

<p><em><strong>In terms of Timothy exchanging a picture card for a truck</strong>, what type of verbal operant does this scenario most closely resemble?</em></p>','2018-10-01 01:30:34','<p>A <strong>mand</strong> is a verbal operant that is under the control of a MO (motivating operation). A &quot;pure&quot; mand occurs soley and spontaneously in the presence of the MO; however, a tact-mand can occur (i.e., you see / smell something yummy and then mand for the stimulus that corresponds to the tact).</p>

